There was excitement at Lagos Island Maternity Hospital, Marina, Lagos, recently, when the Chief Executive Officer of Rainbow Tech Construction Company, Alhaji Waheed Ogunbiyi, celebrated his birthday. Ogunbiyi, who is also the CEO of Oguns Investment and Rainbow Foundation, decided to mark his birthday with hospital patients to give them hope and a sense of belonging. He stressed that it was an obligation for individuals blessed by God to support the needy. He urged the privileged in the society to extend kindness to people in need of welfare. He stated: “I feel excited that today is my birthday. I feel excited that I am here at Lagos Island Maternity Hospital, Marina, to give a token to those who are in need of help. For this year, I have decided to have a low-key celebration and there is none other way to mark it than to be at a hospital.”